<h2 id="editors-notes">Editorâ€™s notes</h2>

<p>Hey friends! Hereâ€™s a guitar lesson for the classic Christmas song â€œO Holy Nightâ€, which is probably my favorite of all holiday tunes. Iâ€™ll be basing this lesson off of the Sufjan Stevens version from 2006, and keeping things as simple as possible when it comes to chords, strumming, and fingerpicking patterns. Whether you want to do a super basic campfire (er, yule log?) version â€“ or do something a bit more advanced with fingerpicking and incorporating the melody riff â€“ this lesson has you covered! I hope you enjoy.</p>

