<h2 id="strumming-patterns">Strumming patterns</h2>

<p>If you want to strum this song, hereâ€™s a few options. I recommend starting light &amp; simple, and then dialing up the intensity as you move along toward the end. Accent &amp; emphasize the 1 and 4 counts!</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 5 + 6 +
D           D               "DOWN..... DOWN....."

1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 5 + 6 +
D   d   d   D   d   d       "DOWN down down, DOWN down down"

1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 5 + 6 +
D   d u d u D   d u d u     "DOWN down-up down-up, DOWN down-up down-up"
</code></pre></div></div>

<h2 id="fingerpicking-options">Fingerpicking options</h2>

<p>You can also fingerpick this song, which Iâ€™ll do by using one (or multiple) of these patterns. I generally keep my right index/middle/ring on the 4th/3rd/2nd strings, and use my right thumb on the bass note of the chord (usually 5th or 6th string). See my video lesson for a demonstration.</p>

