<h2 id="optional-melody-riff-tab-for-intro--first-line-of-the-verse">Optional melody riff tab (for intro / first line of the verse)</h2>

<p>Hereâ€™s a tab I came up with to play the melody of the first line or two â€“ in combination with the chords that go with it. The yellow notes below represent the actually melody notes (i.e. what youâ€™d hum or whistle or sing) â€“ and you can optionally add any amount, or none, of the non-highlighted chord-notes I show below. If you do play the non-highlighted notes, donâ€™t feel pressured to play all of themâ€¦ in other words, its okay if youâ€™re fingerpicking and only play the bass note of the chord, along with the highlighted melody note. See my video lesson for reference!</p>

